com.delphix.masking.api.plugin

Interface MaskingAlgorithm<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of value this Algorithm masks - must be one of the types identified by enums:
    • MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType.STRING
    • MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType.LOCAL_DATE_TIME
    • MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType.BIG_DECIMAL
    • MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType.BYTE_BUFFER
    Attention! If using logger - be careful in choosing the logged information. The sensitive information (to be masked) should never be logged!
    All Superinterfaces:
    MaskingComponent

    public interface MaskingAlgorithm<T>
extends MaskingComponent
    This is the interface all Delphix Masking Algorithms must implement.

    • Method Detail

      • mask

        T mask(@Nullable
       T value)
throws MaskingException
        Method to mask a value of the specified type Attention! This method accesses the value to be masked. This sensitive information should never be logged!
        Parameters:
        value - The value to be masked.
        Returns:
        The masked value. In case of a GenericDataRow type, the returned value will be ignored. In that case the corresponding GenericData object should be modified.
        Throws:
        MaskingException - If an error occurs while masking.

      • listReadOnlyFields

        default java.util.Map<java.lang.String,MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType> listReadOnlyFields()
        Method to list additional fields needed by an algorithm of type GenericDataRow. These fields are read only fields. This is an optional method for GenericDataRow algorithms. In the mask(T) method, these values will be provided in a GenericData object as part of GenericDataRow object.
        Returns:
        Map of name of fields and their types. The type can't be MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType.GENERIC_DATA_ROW.

      • listMaskedFields

        default java.util.Map<java.lang.String,MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType> listMaskedFields()
        Method to list the fields needed by an algorithm of type GenericDataRow for masking. These fields are supposed to be masked. This is required method for GenericDataRow algorithms. In the mask(T) method, these values will be provided in a GenericData object as part of GenericDataRow object. The GenericData object is for each of the field defined by this method. The actual data can be retrieved by calling the appropriate get method on that object.
        Returns:
        Map of name of fields and their types. The type can't be MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType.GENERIC_DATA_ROW.
